Dia. 03 10 Points
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 and 3 are White's \cf1\b privilege\cf0\b0 .
\par As always, the borderlines are made with Xs.
\par
\par White has 12 points, Black has 7 points.
\par After counting (12-7)+(12-7)=\cf1\b 10 points\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Black's sequence with 1, 3 in the \b main diagram\b0  is worth 10 points. Of course, the value is same for White as well.
